respectively, which are included in "all other corporate bonds" in the tables above. at december31, 2012 and 2011, approximately $64million and $81million of these securities,
respectively, or the loans backing such securities, contained guarantees by the u.s. government or a government-sponsored enterprise, and $4million and $10million at
december31, 2012 and 2011, respectively, were comprised of canadian
non-guaranteed securities. the average credit rating of the $389million and $365million of non-guaranteed securities at december31, 2012 and 2011,
respectively, was "aaa" at both dates, and 51% and 71%, respectively, of those securities were issued in 2004 and prior years. the cmbs portfolio is supported by loans that are diversified across
economic sectors and geographical areas. the average credit rating of the cmbs portfolio was "aaa" at both december31, 2012 and 2011.
